# Executive Assistant — 500-Day Story Arcs
# 23 arcs across 500 days (~16.5 months). This middle-duration variant keeps
# the same persona, session structure, and boundary-stressed test surfaces as
# the shorter and longer corpora, while spreading the work enough to show real
# operating rhythm: quarterly earnings and board cycles, monthly close pressure,
# annual planning, sensitive side channels, travel, and quiet periods.
#
# Max concurrent arcs: 4
# Quiet periods: ~late Jun 2026 (family vacation), ~mid-Dec 2026 (holiday +
#                close blackout), ~early Apr 2027 (spring-break family window)
# Rhythm: quarterly earnings cadence (every ~91 days), monthly close (every ~30 days),
#         board meetings (every ~91 days), annual budget cycle (Aug-Dec 2026),
#         Jamie travels ~6-8x/year (board, investor meetings, customer visits)
#
# Session affinity (recall-bench v0.5 §2.7):
#   primarySession: required — where the arc primarily unfolds
#   referencedSessions: optional — sessions echoed at natural touchpoints
#
# IMPORTANT — voice rule for arc/directive content:
#   The agent does not know it's running inside a bounded simulation. Arc
#   titles, descriptions, and directive `event` strings must read like real
#   working context: specific calendar dates, real quarter labels, natural
#   relative time. NEVER write "day 1", "day 250", "the 500-day variant",
#   "the arc", etc. — those bleed into generated memories.
#
# Generation cost (approx, claude-CLI throughput as measured 2026-05-05):
#   ~23 arcs × ~35 selectArcDays touches × ~3-5 min/invocation
#   ≈ 40-65 hours wall-clock total. Roughly 1-2 workweeks of overnight
#   generation, landing naturally between the 180-day and 1000-day corpora.
#
# Calendar rhythm (epoch 2026-01-01):
#   Q1 close + earnings ........ 2026-03-01 → 2026-04-05
#   Q1 board meeting ........... ~2026-03-26
#   Q2 close + earnings ........ 2026-05-30 → 2026-06-29
#   Q2 board meeting ........... ~2026-06-19
#   Family vacation / slowdown . ~2026-06-24 → 2026-07-05
#   Q3 close + earnings ........ 2026-08-29 → 2026-09-28
#   Q3 board meeting ........... ~2026-09-18
#   Annual budget cycle ........ 2026-08-01 → 2026-12-10
#   Exec comp cycle ............ 2026-10-08 → 2026-12-18
#   Holiday + close blackout ... ~2026-12-15 → 2026-12-31
#   Q4 close + earnings ........ 2026-11-28 → 2027-02-02
#   Q4 / FY27 board meeting .... ~2026-12-18
#   Project Condor M&A ......... 2026-04-10 → 2027-02-05
#   Caldwell VIP onsite ........ 2027-02-01 → 2027-02-11 (visit 2027-02-09)
#   Shareholder suit + inquiry . 2027-02-24 → 2027-05-15
#   Q1 FY28 close + earnings ... 2027-03-01 → 2027-04-05
#   Q1 FY28 board meeting ...... ~2027-03-31 → moved to 2027-04-07
#
# Executive Assistant is BOUNDARY-STRESSED. Per spec §2.3.1, arcs scoped
# to an isolated session MUST have that session as primarySession, and
# sensitive content from those sessions must not appear in
# referencedSessions unless explicitly authorized.

